snippet.textDisplay:
"I'm scared of the dentist!"
laughs in endodontist
Imagine getting like 12 shots of numbing so that they can peel back a layer of gum to access your jawbone in order to drill a hole into it to remove an infection and chop off the roots of your tooth's failed root canal as a last ditch effort to save your tooth. And then they shove some bone graft into the hole and sew your gums back up and it's only 30 minutes but absolutely disgusting to think about.

Anyway, I used to be scared of the dentist but now I have an amazing one, which is great because I feel like I get cavities filled (or worse) every damn time I see them.

snippet.textDisplay: I think we should do away with dental insurance and all insurances in that matter. Think about it. If you were a doctor knowing insurance was going to cover the cost of a surgery, you would charge a high amount to your patient because your patient pays for insurance. If there was no insurance, and I mean no insurance at all around the world, which option would you have to choose: don't take care the patient resulting in them finding another doctor (or worse, resulting in their death) and you not getting paid OR you lowering the cost? I have spoken.
